Title: Body Scan Relaxation
Category: Anxiety Grounding

Overview:
The body scan is a mindfulness-based relaxation method that builds awareness of physical tension and promotes gradual relaxation.

When to Use:
- When feeling physically tense
- During stress-related headaches
- Before sleep
- After emotionally difficult events

Steps:
1. Sit or lie comfortably.
2. Focus attention on your feet.
3. Gradually move attention upward through legs, abdomen, chest, arms, shoulders, and head.
4. Notice tension and gently release it.

Why It Works:
Anxiety often manifests as physical tension. By increasing body awareness, individuals can consciously reduce muscle tightness and stress.

Therapeutic Goal:
To reconnect mind and body and reduce stress-related tension.